.TH SP-DRIFT-METRICS 1 "Spherepop Tools" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sp-drift-metrics \- simulate degradation of a metric under adaptive reuse
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-drift-metrics
.RB [ \-t " steps" ]
.RB [ \-s " seed" ]
.RB [ \-o " out.csv" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sp-drift-metrics runs a local simulation illustrating how a metric can drift
away from what it originally tracked when agents adapt to the metric.
.PP
This program is synthetic and non-operational: it does not access external
systems. It only writes CSV output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-t " steps"
Number of time steps (default: 80).
.TP
.BI \-s " seed"
Integer seed (default: 7).
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Output CSV file (default: ./drift.csv).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sp-probe-goodhart(1), sp-check-invariants(1)

